"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92737","Home Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>Police reform is working and crime is falling. Both the independent Crime Survey and police recorded crime show crime has fallen by more than 10 per cent under this coalition government.</p><p> </p><p>England and Wales are safer than they have been for decades with the Crime Survey showing crime at its lowest level since the survey began in 1981.</p><p><br></p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-10-13T15:46:24.9819875Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92737/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92737/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92737/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-09-11","Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of recent trends in the level of crime.","false","Biography information for Chris White","Warwick and Leamington","Chris White","905440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92738","Home Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>This Government is determined to stamp out the abhorrent crime of modern slavery. The Modern Slavery Bill will give law enforcement the tools to tackle modern slavery and enhance support and protection for victims. We will soon publish a comprehensive Modern Slavery Strategy setting out additional practical actions being undertaken.</p><p> </p><p>We will also be introducing a world-leading disclosure requirement to the Bill, which will require big businesses to publicly state each year what action they have taken to ensure their supply chains are slavery free.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-10-13T15:42:33.127295Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92738/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92738/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92738/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-09-11","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to eliminate modern slavery.","false","Biography information for Graham Evans","Weaver Vale","Graham Evans","905439"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92739","Home Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>HMPO experienced higher than expected demand for passports this year. The contingency measures announced by my Rt. hon. Friend, the Home Secretary in June have directly benefited over 30,000 applicants and enabled people to get their passports on time. Full details of overtime and customer compensation payments will be published in HMPO’s next Report and Accounts.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-10-13T15:57:21.9155304Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92739/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92739/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92739/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-09-11","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the cost to her Department of making overtime and compensation payments to people whose passport applications have been delayed.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","905446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92740","Home Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>The Dublin Regulations have allowed the UK to return over 12,000 asylum claimants to other EU countries since coming in to force in 2003. Litigation is a significant factor preventing or delaying transfers – in particular, the ruling of the European Court of Human Rights in 2011 that returns to Greece breached Article 3 of the Convention, halting returns there.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-10-13T15:53:17.7450202Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92740/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92740/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92740/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-09-11","Asylum: Deportation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the reasons are for the reduction in the number of asylum seekers returned under the Dublin Convention in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","905441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92741","Home Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>The Coalition Government is taking decisive action to prevent violence, including violence against women, children and vulnerable people, sexual violence and gang and youth violence. As well as intervening early to prevent violence happening in the first place, we are making sure that victims are supported and perpetrators brought to justice.</p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-10-13T15:58:21.4655607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92741/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92741/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92741/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-09-11","Crimes of Violence: Crime Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to prevent violent crime.","false","Biography information for Mr Stephen Hepburn","Jarrow","Mr Stephen Hepburn","905447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92742","Home Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>The Government has ring-fenced £40 million of stable funding up to 2015 for specialist local domestic and sexual violence support services.</p><p> </p><p>We are committed to supporting local commissioners to make informed decisions about commissioning domestic violence services and are holding a series of regional events to develop expertise in a competitive commissioning environment.</p><p> </p><p>Latest data indicate the number of those charged and conviction rates for domestic abuse are at their highest ever levels.</p><p> </p>","Lewes","Norman Baker",,"2014-10-13T15:55:15.2755511Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92742/answer","Biography information for Norman Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92742/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/92742/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-09-11","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the effect of recent reductions in spending on specialist domestic violence services on the incidence of domestic violence.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","905443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93066","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-10-14","<p>I have been in regular dialogue with the Leeds City Region LEP to discuss their plans for growth. I was pleased to inform this House in July that we have now concluded a Growth Deal with the LEP, which provided the area with a £573 million Government investment. Roger Marsh, the chair of the LEP, described the Deal as a “game-changing moment” for the area.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-10-14T14:13:28.0518075Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93066/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93066/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93066/answer",,,,,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-11","Local Enterprise Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what discussions he has had with the Leeds Local Enterprise Partnership on devolving powers and responsibilities from Whitehall.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","905411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93067","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-10-14","<p>Voter registration is now easier and more convenient than ever before with the launch of online registration. Applying to register to vote now takes as little as 3 minutes and has been a huge success so far – over 90% of users that have provided feedback on the Register to Vote website have said they were ‘satisfied’ or ‘very satisfied’ with the service.</p><p>To date, over 2 million applications have been made under IER with the majority of these made online.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2014-10-14T14:11:24.7675316Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93067/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93067/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93067/answer",,,,,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-11","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the rollout of online individual electoral registration; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond","905410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93068","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-10-14","<p>The Government is committed to maximising electoral registration to help support the highest possible turnout in elections. This includes young people, who we know care deeply about many issues but don’t always express their views at the ballot box.</p><p> </p><p>The introduction of online registration – which is now live in England, Wales and Scotland – brings voter registration into the 21st century and makes it easier, simpler and faster for people to register to vote.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2014-10-14T14:02:20.7529498Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93068/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93068/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93068/answer",,,,,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-11","Voting Behaviour: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what steps the Government plans to take to get more young people registered to vote.","false","Biography information for Julie Hilling","Bolton West","Julie Hilling","905407"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93069","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-10-14","<p>In November last year the Government agreed the Southampton and Portsmouth City Deal with the Local Enterprise Partnership. The deal included a range of infrastructure, skills, business support and labour market schemes.</p><p>Building on this I was delighted to announce a significant Growth Deal worth almost £125 million for the Solent Local Enterprise Partnership in July this year. This includes a substantial commitment for transport improvements in the Fareham and Gosport Peninsula which will cut journey times from Gosport to Portsmouth; investment in local colleges; the establishment of a Land and Property Board that will secure the release of public land; and additional investment in business support services.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-10-14T13:52:49.3370495Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93069/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93069/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93069/answer",,,,,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-11","Local Enterprise Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what discussions he has had with the Solent Local Enterprise Partnership on devolving powers and responsibilities from Whitehall.","false","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","905405"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93070","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-10-14","<p>I have had no reports on the removal of people from the electoral register in Scotland on the grounds that they were additionally registered elsewhere.</p><p> </p><p>People are free to register in more than one place if it appears to the relevant Registration Officers that they are resident in that area.</p><p> </p><p>The Electoral Commission has produced guidance on this issue to assist Registration Officers in effectively carrying out their duties.</p><p> </p><p>However, it is ultimately a matter for the local Registration Officer to determine whether an individual is resident at a particular address, taking into account relevant circumstances of the particular case.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2014-10-14T14:15:14.788595Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93070/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93070/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93070/answer",,,,,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-11","Electoral Register: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, whether he has received a report from electoral registration officers in Scotland on removal of people from the electoral register on the grounds that they are additionally registered elsewhere; what guidance he issues to electoral registration officers on how to use their discretion when registering residents; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Fiona Mactaggart","Slough","Fiona Mactaggart","905412"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93071","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-10-14","<p>The North East LEP Growth Deal provided £6m towards a £23m Rural Growth Network project which will improve infrastructure in key rural market towns helping to grow innovative, community-led networks of rural enterprise hubs to support rural business growth.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-10-14T14:04:23.2974273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93071/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93071/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93071/answer",,,,,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-11","Rural Areas: Northumberland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, what support his Department  provides for rural Northumberland.","false","Biography information for Guy Opperman","Hexham","Guy Opperman","905409"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93440","Scotland Office","false","2014-10-15","<p>The Scotland Office is part of the Scottish Employability Forum, where we work jointly with the Scottish Government and Cosla on employment issues and which will next meet in November.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-10-15T14:17:25.9049915Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93440/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93440/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93440/answer",,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-09-11","Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent discussions he has had with the First Minister in Scotland on jobs.","false","Biography information for Jim Sheridan","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Jim Sheridan","905369"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93441","Scotland Office","false","2014-10-15","<p>Scotland Office officials attend regular meetings with the Scottish Assessors Association’s Electoral Registration Committee to discuss electoral registration issues in Scotland. In addition, Cabinet Office officials have been in regular contact and have met with electoral registration officers to discuss the implementation of individual electoral registration in Scotland.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-10-15T14:38:04.6201245Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93441/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93441/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93441/answer",,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-09-11","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with electoral registration officers in Scotland about changes they have made in 2014 to the electoral register; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Fiona Mactaggart","Slough","Fiona Mactaggart","905366"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93442","Scotland Office","false","2014-10-15","<p>I speak regularly with Ministerial colleagues in Defra on fisheries matters, and the UK Government keeps in close contact with the Scottish Government to ensure that the interests of the Scottish fishing industry are reflected in discussions on both UK and intra-UK fishing entitlements.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-10-15T14:33:27.2905546Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93442/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93442/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93442/answer",,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-09-11","Fisheries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with his (a) Ministerial colleagues and (b) counterparts in the Scottish Government on the future balance of fishing entitlements available to the UK and its effect on Scotland.","false","Biography information for Andrew George","St Ives","Andrew George","905367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93443","Scotland Office","false","2014-10-15","<p>I refer the hon Gentleman to the answer I gave to the hon Members for Stroud, Linlithgow and East Falkirk, Livingston, and Congleton earlier today.</p><p> </p>","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael",,"2014-10-15T14:21:13.0348274Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93443/answer","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93443/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93443/answer",,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-09-11","Constitutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent assessment he has made of Scotland's constitutional future.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","905370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93444","Scotland Office","false","2014-10-15","<p>I am in regular contact with my Rt hon Friend the Secretary of State for Transport on a range of issues including on-going work on options for further capacity and journey time improvements between northern England and Scotland.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-10-15T14:28:22.5224658Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93444/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93444/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93444/answer",,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-09-11","Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Transport on long-term plans for rail connectivity between Newcastle and Edinburgh.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","905371"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93445","Scotland Office","false","2014-10-15","<p>Scotland made the decision to remain part of the UK family – part of an economy that is expected to grow faster than any other G7 country this year, with a falling deficit and record numbers of people in work. We are part of a large and resilient economy that provides stability, opportunities and more prosperity to people and businesses in Scotland.</p><p> </p>","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael",,"2014-10-15T14:30:24.5717218Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93445/answer","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93445/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93445/answer",,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-09-11","Sovereignty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what assessment he has made of the effect of the result of the Scottish independence referendum on the Scottish economy.","false","Biography information for Jim McGovern","Dundee West","Jim McGovern","905372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93446","Scotland Office","false","2014-10-15","<p>The Scotland Act 2012 gave tax raising powers to the Scottish Parliament, including full devolution of stamp duty land tax and landfill tax, starting from April 2015. The Scottish Government has taken forward legislation to replace these taxes in Scotland.</p><p>Lord Smith’s Commission will consider proposals to devolve further tax raising powers.</p><p> </p>","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael",,"2014-10-15T14:35:49.5456844Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93446/answer","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93446/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/93446/answer",,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-09-11","Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with the Scottish Government on extending the tax powers of the Scottish Parliament.","false","Biography information for Iain Stewart","Milton Keynes South","Iain Stewart","905368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91342","Attorney General","false","2014-10-13","<p>On 18 August 2014 the Prime Minister announced that the family test was being formalised as part of the impact assessment for all domestic policies. From October 2014, every new domestic policy will be examined for its impact on the family.</p><p> </p>","South Swindon","Mr Robert Buckland",,"2014-10-13T14:22:11.0212077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91342/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91342/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91342/answer",,,,,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-09-10","Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, with reference to the Prime Minister's speech of 15 August 2011 calling for a family test to be applied to all domestic policy, which policies of the Law Officers' Departments have been so assessed to date.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","208844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91343","Attorney General","false","2014-10-13","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) does not collect specific data on suspects referred to the CPS for a charging decision where child sexual abuse is alleged. However, data is available for the number of defendants whose prosecution was completed, where the case has been flagged as child abuse, and where the principal offence at finalisation is categorised as a sexual offence.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The CPS definition of child abuse covers any case where the victim was under 18 years of age at the time of the offence and includes allegations of crimes perpetrated by both adults and under 18s.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>During each of the last five years the number of defendants prosecuted, in cases flagged as child abuse and whose principal offence was identified as a sexual offence, is as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>Convictions</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>Unsuccessful</strong></p></td><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>TOTAL</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>Volume</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>%</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Volume</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>%</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2009-2010</strong></p></td><td><p>3,133</p></td><td><p>75.7%</p></td><td><p>1,004</p></td><td><p>24.3%</p></td><td><p><strong>4,137</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2010-2011</strong></p></td><td><p>3,551</p></td><td><p>74.1%</p></td><td><p>1,243</p></td><td><p>25.9%</p></td><td><p><strong>4,794</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011-2012</strong></p></td><td><p>3,530</p></td><td><p>75.8%</p></td><td><p>1,125</p></td><td><p>24.2%</p></td><td><p><strong>4,655</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012-2013</strong></p></td><td><p>3,070</p></td><td><p>75.8%</p></td><td><p>981</p></td><td><p>24.2%</p></td><td><p><strong>4,051</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013-2014</strong></p></td><td><p>3,344</p></td><td><p>76.5%</p></td><td><p>1,027</p></td><td><p>23.5%</p></td><td><p><strong>4,371</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3"><p>Data Source: CPS Case Management Information System</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>It is not possible to disaggregate figures to show separately the volume and outcome of proceedings for individual offences within the Sexual Offences Category. A single defendant may be charged with more than one offence.</p><p> </p>","South Swindon","Mr Robert Buckland",,"2014-10-13T14:20:51.8179597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91343/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91343/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91343/answer",,,,,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-09-10","Offences against Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many referrals were made to the Crown Prosecution Service by the police regarding child sexual offences in each of the last five years; and in how many such cases there were subsequent (a) prosecutions and (b) convictions.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","209019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91344","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-13","<p>The analysis is currently being updated in light of information and evidence provided by stakeholders and will be published alongside the regulations in the autumn.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-10-13T13:54:33.5458432Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91344/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91344/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91344/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-09-10","Disabled Students' Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when his Department will publish an assessment of the effect on disabled people of the proposed changes to disabled students' allowances.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","208957"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91345","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-06","<p>The Government currently proposes that section 74 of the Enterprise and Regulatory Reform Act 2013 (“ERRA”) is implemented on 6 April 2018.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is consulting on this proposed timing. This consultation closes on 27 October 2014 and full details of the consultation are available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/transitional-provisions-for-the-repeal-of-section-52-of-the-cdpa" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/transitional-provisions-for-the-repeal-of-section-52-of-the-cdpa</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Accordingly, the Secretary of State currently has no plans to make a statement.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2014-10-06T09:58:47.2840801Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91345/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91345/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91345/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-09-10","Enterprise and Regulatory Reform Act 2013","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what his Department's planned timeline is for the implementation of section 74 of the Enterprise and Regulatory Reform Act 2013; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","209011"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91346","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-06","<p>The Government currently proposes that section 74 of the Enterprise and Regulatory Reform Act 2013 (“ERRA”) is implemented on 6 April 2018, which it views is a fair and proportionate transition period. Its assessment of the adequacy of the transition period, based on available evidence, is set out in the consultation-stage Impact Assessment.</p><p> </p><p>This proposal for the transition period is subject to consultation. The consultation was launched on 15 September 2014 and will close on 27 October 2014. The consultation document and its associated Impact Assessment are available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/transitional-provisions-for-the-repeal-of-section-52-of-the-cdpa" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/transitional-provisions-for-the-repeal-of-section-52-of-the-cdpa</a>. The Government will make its final assessment of the most appropriate transition period following the consultation.</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2014-10-06T09:39:29.4232262Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91346/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91346/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91346/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-09-10","Enterprise and Regulatory Reform Act 2013","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of the planned transition period for the implementation of section 74 of the Enterprise and Regulatory Reform Act 2013.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","209012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91348","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-01","<p>On 18 August 2014 my Rt. Hon. Friend the Prime Minister announced that the family test was being formalised as part of the impact assessment for all domestic policies. From October 2014, every new domestic policy will be examined for its impact on the family.</p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-10-01T12:48:58.0063385Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91348/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91348/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91348/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-09-10","Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the Prime Minister's speech of 15 August 2011 calling for a family test to be applied to all domestic policy, which policies of his Department have been so assessed to date.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","208843"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91349","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-13","<p>Ministers and officials have been engaged in extensive discussions with stakeholders, students and their representatives and disability organisations since April this year. The views and evidence provided have informed proposals and the on-going Equality Analysis.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-10-13T13:56:42.1395509Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91349/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91349/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91349/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-09-10","Disabled Students' Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether his Department will carry out a public consultation on proposed changes to disabled students' allowances.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","208891"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91350","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-13","<p>We expect to publish the draft regulations. Discussions with stakeholders, students and their representatives were held over the summer.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-10-13T13:45:32.0089703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91350/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91350/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91350/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-09-10","Disabled Students' Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when he plans to publish draft regulations for the proposed changes to disabled students allowance; and for how long a consultation on such changes will run.","false","Biography information for Lord Blunkett","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Mr David Blunkett","208899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91351","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-09-15","<p>No formal complaints were received about the allocation of funding from the Innovation Fund.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2014-09-15T15:40:37.6869832Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91351/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91351/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91351/answer",,,,,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-10","Innovation Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, from which organisation complaints have been received about the allocation of funding from the Innovation Fund.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","208876"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91352","Cabinet Office","false","2014-10-15","<p>On 18 August 2014 the Prime Minister announced that the family test was being formalised as part of the impact assessment for all domestic policies. From October 2014, every new domestic policy will be examined for its impact on the family.</p><p> </p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin",,"2014-10-15T16:13:22.6110385Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91352/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91352/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91352/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-09-10","Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to the Prime Minister's speech of 15 August 2011 calling for a family test to be applied to all domestic policy, which policies of his Department have been so assessed to date.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","208845"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91353","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-09-16","<p>The results of the nationwide test of datamatching between government records and electoral registers is available at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-confirming-electors-through-data-matching" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evaluation-confirming-electors-through-data-matching</a></p><p>An evaluation report on the datamatching taking place this summer is due to be published in late autumn.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2014-09-16T10:33:38.8390931Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91353/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91353/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91353/answer",,,,,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-10","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, if he will place a report in the Library every week of what proportion of the Spring 2014 electorate have been successfully datamatched for the transition to the Individual Electoral Register using (a) the DWP CIS database and (b) additional datamatching employed by local authorities in each local authority.","false","Biography information for Stephen Twigg","Liverpool, West Derby","Stephen Twigg","208872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91354","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-09-16","<p>Data concerning the volumes of online and paper applications received, which can be interrogated by date, is available at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/performance/register-to-vote" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/performance/register-to-vote</a></p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2014-09-16T10:30:15.489658Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91354/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91354/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91354/answer",,,,,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-09-10","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, if he will place a report in the Library every week of the number of voter registration requests made via the new online registration service in each local authority.","false","Biography information for Stephen Twigg","Liverpool, West Derby","Stephen Twigg","208873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91355","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-06","<p>Your letter of 31 July 2014 asks for a response to your previous letter of 18 June 2014, which was responded to by HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) in their letter to you dated 29 July 2014. HMRC replied to the letter of 31 July 2014 on 30 September 2014.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-10-06T14:17:11.866121Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91355/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91355/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91355/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-10","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he intends to reply to the letter dated 31 July 2014 from the right hon. Member for Manchester, Gorton with regard to Mr Godfrey Jones, transferred by the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Kaufman","Manchester, Gorton","Sir Gerald Kaufman","208869"
