"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91357","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-23","<p>At the time of the collapse of Landsbanki and its UK branch, Icesave, customer deposits amounted to £4.5bn. Depositors were fully compensated at the time of the collapse by the Financial Services Compensation Scheme (FSCS) and the Government. In return, the FSCS became a priority creditor in the Landsbanki estate, which is currently being wound down.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-09-23T10:40:59.1876215Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91357/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91357/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91357/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-10","Landsbanki","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if HM Treasury will limit the amount of compensation paid to UK Icesave customers.","false","Biography information for Stephen Metcalfe","South Basildon and East Thurrock","Stephen Metcalfe","208878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91358","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-23","<p>The 2010 Spending Review allocated up to £1.5 billion to the Equitable Life Payment Scheme. The Government has no plans to review the level of funding available to the Payment Scheme.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","208880","2014-09-23T10:51:23.7991656Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91358/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91358/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91358/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-10","Equitable Life Assurance Society: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he last reviewed the amount of compensation made available to Equitable Life policyholders and annuitants through the Equitable Life Payment Scheme.","false","Biography information for Stephen Metcalfe","South Basildon and East Thurrock","Stephen Metcalfe","208879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91359","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-23","<p>The 2010 Spending Review allocated up to £1.5 billion to the Equitable Life Payment Scheme. The Government has no plans to review the level of funding available to the Payment Scheme.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","208879","2014-09-23T10:51:23.8796415Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91359/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91359/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91359/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-10","Equitable Life Assurance Society: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, under what circumstances he would review the amount of compensation made available to Equitable Life policyholders through the Equitable Life Payment Scheme.","false","Biography information for Stephen Metcalfe","South Basildon and East Thurrock","Stephen Metcalfe","208880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91360","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-13","<p>The Government do not publish outturn or forecast data for expenditure on infrastructure projects as a proportion of Gross Domestic Product.</p><p> </p><p>The Office for Budget Responsibility publishes historical data on public sector gross investment (PSGI) as a percentage of GDP— this can be accessed at the following address;</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/pubs/PSF_aggregates_databank_Aug_2014.xls" target="_blank">http://budgetresponsibility.org.uk/pubs/PSF_aggregates_databank_Aug_2014.xls</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Further information on infrastructure investment can be found in the National Infrastructure Plan 2013, which is available on the Infrastructure UK website.</p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-10-13T15:13:07.9127974Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91360/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91360/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91360/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-10","Infrastructure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what proportion of Gross Domestic Product the Government spent on nationally significant infrastructure projects in each year since 1997.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","208915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91361","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-23","<p>In her report the Parliamentary Ombudsman was clear that the state of the public purse should be taken into account when deciding the level of funding available. The Government decided that £1.5billion was an appropriate level of funding for the Equitable Life Payment Scheme.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-09-23T10:49:41.2844216Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91361/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91361/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91361/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-10","Equitable Life Assurance Society: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what criteria he used to calculate the amount of compensation issued to Equitable Life policyholders through the Equitable Life Payment Scheme.","false","Biography information for Stephen Metcalfe","South Basildon and East Thurrock","Stephen Metcalfe","208882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91362","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-13","<p>The total number of NINo registrations to adult overseas nationals entering the UK in 2012/13 was: 562,000 and in 2013/14 it was: 603,000.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-10-13T10:25:50.3298231Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91362/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91362/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91362/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-10","National Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people were allocated a National Insurance number in (a) 2012-13 and (b) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","208839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91363","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-15","<p><strong>The Government has received a number of representations enclosing documents relating to the ‘Cut Tourism VAT’ campaign, which seeks a reduced rate of VAT for accommodation and attractions. </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>I refer the Rt Hon gentleman to my comments during the Westminster Hall debate on 11<sup>th</sup> February 2014.</strong></p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-10-15T14:52:33.9582543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91363/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91363/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91363/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-10","Tourism: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent representations he has received from the tourism industry on the level of VAT applicable to leisure attractions in the UK; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","208988"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91364","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-15","<p>The Government issued guidance accompanying the statutory instrument (2013 no. 395) implementing the Late Payment Directive (2011/7/EU).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The guidance can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/360834/bis-14-1116-a-users-guide-to-the-recast-late-payment-directive.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/360834/bis-14-1116-a-users-guide-to-the-recast-late-payment-directive.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-10-15T13:46:22.0212943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91364/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91364/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91364/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91364/answer/previousversion/21555","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91364/answer/previousversion/21555",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-09-10","Business: Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what guidance he has issued on how the amended Commercial Debts (Interest) Act 1998 should comply with Directive 2011/7/EU in helping to combat late payments in commercial transactions.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","208911"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91365","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-23","<p>The Funding for Lending Scheme (FLS) provides funding to banks and building societies for an extended period, with both the price and quantity of funding provided linked to their lending performance. There is no mechanical link between funding drawn from the scheme and lending activity in any particular nation, region or city. The decision on where, how much and to whom to lend remains a commercial decision for the bank or building society concerned. More generally, the FLS has been successful in helping to reduce bank funding costs to historic lows; and in providing strong incentives for participants to make loans cheaper and more easily available.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Ministers meet with various stakeholders to discuss a broad range of issues. It is not appropriate to reveal the detail of these discussions or to release any information exchanged which may pertain to the FLS. Barclays participated in the first phase of the FLS, which ran until January 2014, but are not participating in the Scheme’s extension. Barclays’ FLS data is publically available on the Bank of England’s website: http://www.bankofengland.co.uk/markets/Pages/FLS/default.aspx</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","209064 ; 209065","2014-09-23T10:46:40.7301847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91365/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91365/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91365/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-09-10","Banks: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of the Funding for Lending Scheme on the lending market in (a) Southend and (b) England and Wales; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Mr David Amess","209063"
