"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91165","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>We continue to consult closely with other members of the coalition on how to defeat ISIL. The UK, France and Germany have all provided equipment to the Kurds.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-13T15:12:02.5212472Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91165/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91165/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91165/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Kurds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his French and German counterparts about assistance to the Kurdistan regional government.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","208638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91166","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>We have not undertaken a formal assessment of the security threat to Israel from Hamas.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-13T15:21:02.4516175Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91166/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91166/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91166/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the security threat to Israel from Hamas.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","208639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91167","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>I raised the issue of Gaza with the Israeli Justice Minister, the Intelligence Minister and the Deputy Foreign Minister on 6 October during my visit to Israel and the Occupied Palestinian Territories from 6-8 October. Our Ambassador to Tel Aviv has also raised this issue with senior officials in the Israeli Prime Minister’s Office and National Security Council on 7 and 8 Sept.</p><p>Israeli restrictions on the movements of goods and people do tremendous damage to the economy and living standards of ordinary people in Gaza and only serve to strengthen, not weaken, Hamas.</p><p>UK Ministers and senior officials have consistently urged Israel to further ease its restrictions on Gaza. An improved economy is not only essential to ease the suffering of the people, including the children, of Gaza, but firmly in Israel’s security interests.</p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-13T15:24:00.7826617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91167/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91167/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91167/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to the Israeli authorities on the entry to Gaza of construction materials.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208640"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91168","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>A UNSC resolution or the consent of a government are not the only potential bases in international law for the use of force. Other legal bases would include: individual or collective self-defence; and, in certain exceptional circumstances, in order to avert an overwhelming humanitarian catastrophe. ISIL continue to pose a direct threat to Iraq. They operate across the borders of Syria and Iraq, in a situation where the Government of Syria is unable or unwilling to take effective action to counter the threat posed by ISIL. Iraq has requested help to defend itself. The US have been clear that in carrying out military actions in Syria they are acting on the basis of both collective and individual self-defence. If the UK were to undertake military strikes in Syria we would only do so on a sound legal basis and that would depend on the facts on the ground at the time, for example in line with the US led international efforts in collective self defence pursuant to the Iraqi request of 20 September. The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), has been clear that if the decision were made to take military action in Syria the government would return to the House of Commons. However, if there were a critical British interest at stake or there were the need to take urgent action to prevent a humanitarian catastrophe then it would be possible to order that and come straight to the House and explain afterwards.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-13T15:16:47.7997148Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91168/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91168/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91168/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Iraq and Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will take steps to ensure all UN member states commit not to take military action in Iraq or Syria without either the consent of the governments of those countries or a supporting UNSC Resolution.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","208633"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91169","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>I raised the issue of Gaza with the Israeli Justice Minister, the Intelligence Minister and the Deputy Foreign Minister on 6 October during my visit to Israel and the Occupied Palestinian Territories from 6-8 October. Our Ambassador to Tel Aviv has also raised this issue with senior officials in the Israeli Prime Minister’s Office and National Security Council on 7 and 8 Sept.</p><p>Israeli restrictions on the movements of goods and people do tremendous damage to the economy and living standards of ordinary people in Gaza and only serve to strengthen, not weaken, Hamas.</p><p>UK Ministers and senior officials have consistently urged Israel to further ease its restrictions on Gaza. An improved economy is not only essential to ease the suffering of the people, including the children, of Gaza, but firmly in Israel’s security interests</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-13T15:35:13.6969735Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91169/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91169/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91169/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to the Israeli government on an end to the blockade of Gaza.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91170","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-29","Our Consulate-General in Jerusalem met with the Palestinian Prime Minister on 8 September to discuss the issue of reconstruction in Gaza.","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-29T14:36:06.1604541Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91170/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91170/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91170/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with the Palestinian Authority about reconstruction in Gaza.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","208679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91171","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-10","<p>It is deeply tragic that so many UNRWA personnel were killed in the recent escalation in violence in Gaza. There must be meaningful investigations into possible violations of international human rights law and international humanitarian law by all sides, including those committed by Hamas and other militant groups. We are calling on both sides to cooperate with the Commission of Inquiry set up by the UN Human Rights Council, which must itself be independent and balanced in its approach.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-10T14:39:59.2998041Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91171/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91171/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91171/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what support the Government is giving to the UN's call for accountability from the Israeli authorities for deaths in Gaza of UNRWA personnel, medical staff, firefighters and technicians, injuries to aid workers and the damage or destruction of UN premises and hospitals and clinics.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91172","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-09-12","<p>We are currently considering the merits of a request for funding that we received from the UK National Committee for Women on the 28<sup>th</sup> of August.</p><p> </p><p>The UK is the second largest donor to UN Women, providing £12.5m of funding each year.</p><p> </p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-09-12T15:00:54.6545641Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91172/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91172/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91172/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-09-09","UN Women","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will allocate funding to support the work of UN Women UK.","false","Biography information for Dr Roberta Blackman-Woods","City of Durham","Roberta Blackman-Woods","208687"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91173","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) committed to work in advance of the Summit to: secure high level overseas attendance, ensure that foreign governments make commitments to end female genital mutilation (FGM) and child, early and forced marriage (CEFM), and lobby countries to sign the Girl Summit Charter. The FCO engaged over 70 of its diplomatic missions, working closely with the Department for International Development. This resulted in over 800 participants attending the Summit from 50 countries, including over 30 ministers; 36 countries signing the Summit Charter so far; and commitments to action from nearly 150 governments, organisations and individuals to date. <br> <br>The FCO is committed to building on the success of the Summit and will continue to lobby more states to sign the Charter and to continue to make commitments to end FGM and CEFM.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2014-10-13T13:29:21.933647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91173/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91173/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91173/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Females: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to monitor the effectiveness of the commitments given by his Department during the Girls Summit 2014.","false","Biography information for Dr Roberta Blackman-Woods","City of Durham","Roberta Blackman-Woods","208693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91174","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>The UK is working closely with the US, European and regional partners on Gaza to support Egyptian efforts to secure a negotiated settlement that includes the opening up of legitimate movement and access in and out of Gaza. The United Nations Security Council has an important role to play in supporting Egyptian efforts. That is why the UK, France and Germany have worked closely on elements for a Security Council Resolution. Discussions continue in New York to take this work forward.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-13T14:24:25.4907313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91174/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91174/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91174/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent steps the Government has taken to help to end the blockade of Gaza.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91175","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>We welcome the announcement on Tuesday 26 August of agreement by all parties to a ceasefire, and pay tribute to the Government of Egypt for their work to secure this important step.</p><p>It is now vital that the parties engage in negotiations to reach a sustainable and durable agreement which tackles the underlying causes of the conflict. It is only this which will put a stop to the cycle of violence. We are clear that there should be international monitoring and verification to ensure implementation of a comprehensive agreement.</p><p>The UK, France and Germany have worked closely on elements for a Security Council Resolution. Discussions continue in New York to take this work forward.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-13T14:25:49.578815Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91175/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91175/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91175/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the role of international observers in monitoring ceasefire arrangements in Gaza and protecting the security of Palestinians and Israelis.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208649"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91176","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>We continue regularly to ask Israel to build on its progress towards implementation of the second report of the Turkel Commission and fully adopt its recommendations. Most recently, an official from our Embassy in Tel Aviv raised this issue with the Israeli Military Advocate General on 9 September.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-13T15:05:09.7237266Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91176/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91176/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91176/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Israel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations his Department has made to the government of Israel on implementation of the findings of the Turkel Commission.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91177","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>The Government has worked hard with our international partners to help bring about a sustainable ceasefire – and we warmly welcome the agreement reached in Cairo for a ceasefire. We pay tribute to the Government of Egypt for their work in securing this important step and we continue to monitor the situation closely.</p><p>The ceasefire provides the space for reaching a comprehensive agreement that tackles the underlying causes of the conflict. We are urging the parties to now quickly resume negotiations to that end.</p><p>The UK will do all it can in the UN to support efforts to create a ceasefire which is sustainable and durable. We are currently working on a UNSCR in New York to that end.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-13T14:29:00.5751831Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91177/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91177/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91177/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Middle East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what contribution his Department made to the Egyptian-mediated negotiations between Israel and the Palestinians on achieving a sustainable ceasefire.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91178","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-10","<p>The UK is working closely with international partners to secure immediate and unimpeded humanitarian access to Gaza, to deliver much-needed aid to its people. We are also backing Egyptian efforts to secure a durable ceasefire. In this reqard, we are working with international partners to support the establishment of a monitoring and verification mechanism to underpin any ceasefire agreement.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-10T14:45:21.4221461Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91178/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91178/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91178/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the Government is taking (a) unilaterally and (b) multilaterally to achieve the aims set out in the Foreign Affairs Council conclusions of 15 August 2014 of (i) immediate and unimpeded humanitarian access to Gaza and (ii) the lifting of the Gaza closure regime.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91179","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-10","<p>The UK strongly supports the European External Action Service's work to produce an options paper for EU support for a sustainable ceasefire. This paper will include options for a potential EU role in monitoring and verification, and the possibility of reactivating and perhaps expanding the mandate of EUBAM Rafah. Work is continuing in Brussels, and the UK is encouraging the EEAS to put forward detailed and ambitious options.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-10T14:38:46.3727037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91179/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91179/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91179/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the timetable is for the study of options for an internationally-supervised mechanism to enable full access and movement through all Gaza ports of entry agreed at the Foreign Affairs Council of 15 August 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91180","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-10-13","<p>We welcomed the announcement on the formation of a new interim technocratic government for the Occupied Palestinian Territories. Reuniting Gaza and the West Bank under a government committed to peace is a necessary condition for resolving the Israel-Palestinian conflict.</p><p>The UK Government fully supports the Palestinian Authority’s efforts to regain control of Gaza and restore effective and accountable governance.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2014-10-13T15:29:29.5386015Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91180/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91180/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91180/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what support the Government is giving to the efforts of the Palestinian National Unity Government to reconnect Gaza and the West Bank.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91181","Department of Health","false","2014-10-13","<p>The Department has secured funds and is working with the Health and Social Care Information Centre to commission a new survey. The survey is currently being scoped and is expected to be put out to tender later in the year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-10-13T15:45:15.8098125Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91181/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91181/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91181/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-09","Mental Health Services: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what progress has been made on plans to develop a new prevalence survey for Child and Adolescent Mental Health Services.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","208642"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91182","Department of Health","false","2014-09-12","<p> </p><p>The Department only provides funding to the five financial support schemes which provide support to people infected with HIV and/or hepatitis C as a result of treatment with contaminated National Health Service supplied blood or blood products.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Macfarlane Trust, the Eileen Trust and the Caxton Foundation are given an annual budget allocation and are required to operate within the budget envelope of that allocation and any reserves they may hold. The Department provides MFET Ltd and the Skipton Fund with sufficient funds to meet all legitimate claims for the payments that they are mandated to make. In the last five years, the Department has received one business case for additional funding from the Macfarlane Trust, and one from the Caxton Foundation.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-09-12T10:26:33.8791491Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91182/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91182/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91182/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-09","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many times his Department has received applications for (a) additional funding or (b) other support from the funds and trusts which provide support to people with contaminated blood in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","208727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91183","Department of Health","false","2014-09-12","<p> </p><p>We do not centrally hold information on the locations where mental health patients have been sent for out-of-area treatments since May 2010.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-09-12T13:04:31.4994226Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91183/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91183/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91183/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-09","Mental Health Services: Out of Area Treatment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, in which locations mental health patients have been sent for out-of-area treatments since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Steve Rotheram","Liverpool, Walton","Steve Rotheram","208736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91184","Department of Health","false","2014-10-14","<p>I refer the honourable Member to the answer given by my hon. friend (Jane Ellison) of 7 July 2014, Official Report, Col. 38W to the hon. Member for Congleton.</p><p> </p><p>www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201415/cmhansrd/cm140707/text/140707w0002.htm#14070761002001</p><p> </p><p>Paragraph 2.1 in the Scientific Report of the Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority (HFEA) expert panel also describes the function of mitochondrial DNA. This report can be found on the HFEA’s Website at:</p><p> </p><p>www.hfea.gov.uk/6372.html</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2014-10-14T15:37:21.4097586Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91184/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91184/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91184/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-09","DNA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what information his Department holds on the role of mitrochondrial DNA in addition to energy-related functions.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","208700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91185","Home Office","false","2014-09-12","<p /> <p>The Salvation Army has been delivering support to victims of human trafficking since July 2011. They publish an annual report which summarises their activity over the year (July-June), including the number, region and countries of origin of male and female victims. The reports for 2011-12 and 2012-13 can be found on The Salvation Army’s website here: <a href="http://www.salvationarmy.org.uk/uki/Anti_Human_Trafficking_Latest_Report" target="_blank">http://www.salvationarmy.org.uk/uki/Anti_Human_Trafficking_Latest_Report</a>.</p><p /> <p>The report for 2013-14 will be published later this year.</p><p />","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-09-12T14:57:55.4753436Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91185/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91185/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91185/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-09-09","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what data her Department holds on the number, region and countries of origin of male and female victims of modern slavery and human trafficking who have been referred to the Salvation Army in the last 10 years; if she will publish the data in a medium which hon. Members can readily access; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","208741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91186","Home Office","false","2014-09-17","<p /> <p>The Secretary of State for the Home Department, my right hon. Friend the Member for Maidenhead (Mrs May) made the decision to terminate the contract with Raytheon, which was negotiated and signed by the last Government. <br><br>I refer the hon. Member to the written ministerial statement made by my right hon. Friend the Member for Ashford (Mr Green) on 22 July 2010, Official Report, columns 44-45WS, regarding the termination of the e-Borders contract.</p><p />","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-09-17T15:15:39.8969344Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91186/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91186/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91186/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-09-09","Borders: Personal Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, which Minister in her Department took the decision to terminate the contract with Raytheon to build an immigration computer system; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","208634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91187","Home Office","false","2014-09-17","<p /> <p>The UK definition of terrorism is contained in section 1 of the Terrorism Act 2000. Safeguards are built in to our legislation. The police and the Crown Prosecution Service are required to ensure that prosecutions are only pursued in appropriate cases, where there is sufficient evidence and it is in the public interest to do so. <br><br>David Anderson QC, the Independent Reviewer of Terrorism Legislation, has made four specific recommendations in respect of the definition in his most recent Annual Report on the Operation of the Terrorism Acts in 2013, which was laid in Parliament on 22nd July. We are currently considering these in detail and will respond in due course.</p><p />","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2014-09-17T15:19:23.7097741Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91187/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91187/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91187/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-09-09","Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will commission an assessment of the effect on civil liberties of current statutory definitions of terrorism and the proportionality and necessity of the range of those definitions.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","208686"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91188","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-13","<p>The UK is one of the biggest donors to the Gaza crisis, providing more than £17 million of emergency assistance. All of our support is being channelled through UN agencies, international organisations and UK non-governmental organisations.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2014-10-13T16:42:00.7308602Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91188/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91188/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91188/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the increase in UK aid to Gaza (a) directly and (b) through contributions to UK non-governmental organisations and to international organisations has been since the start of Operation Protective Edge.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91189","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-13","<p>DFID, along with key partner agencies like UNRWA, is still assessing the level of damage to facilities in Gaza. The current priority is to ensure there is progress in the talks in Cairo.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2014-10-13T16:43:03.5589503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91189/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91189/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91189/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what representations she has made to the Israeli government on reparations for the damage caused by Operation Protective Edge to UN and civilian facilities in Gaza.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91190","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-13","<p>Initial reports from the UN Relief and Works Agency indicate that four schools built using DFID funding sustained damage during the conflict. The office of one of our implementing partners was also damaged. Assessments are continuing to establish the extent and the exact cause of the damage.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2014-10-13T16:37:33.312959Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91190/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91190/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91190/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what projects funded by her Department in Gaza have been (a) damaged and (b) destroyed as a result of Israeli military action during Operation Protective Edge.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91191","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-13","<p>The UK pledged to contribute £20 million. We are clear, however, that reconstruction in Gaza will require a durable ceasefire, an agreed approach on security, predictable and sustained access for people and goods in and out of Gaza, and good governance arrangements.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2014-10-13T16:38:22.8124158Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91191/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91191/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91191/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what contribution her Department will offer at the donors' conference on the reconstruction of Gaza.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208654"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91192","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-13","<p>An airport or seaport could help to facilitate trade but the extent of their importance would depend on the lifting of restrictions on exports and transfers to Gaza’s natural markets of Israel and the West Bank. We have consistently called on the Government of Israel to improve movement and access into and out of Gaza, and will continue to do so.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2014-10-13T16:39:37.0398631Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91192/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91192/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91192/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-09","Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the importance to a sustainable economy in Gaza of the re-opening of (a) Gaza airport and (b) the sea-port.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","208655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91193","Department for International Development","false","2014-10-13","<p>The particular information requested is not collected centrally and is not available without incurring disproportionate costs. The UK Government is committed to increasing focus on girls and women across all our investments to ‘stop poverty before it starts’ by creating environments that unlock their voices, choices and control, and that empowers them economically.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Since May 2014, under the International Development (Gender Equality) Act 2014, DFID is required to give regard to the contribution its assistance is likely to make to reducing gender inequality, or to gender-related differences in needs, before assistance is provided.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-10-13T15:03:33.4791965Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91193/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91193/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91193/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-09-09","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much her Department has spent on projects solely for the benefit of (a) males and (b) females in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","208716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91194","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-10-14","<p>Drug offending is serious in itself and drug abuse also underlies a huge volume of acquisitive and violent crime which can blight communities. The independent Sentencing Council issued a sentencing guideline on drug offences, effective from February 2012, which brought sentencing guidance together for the first time to help to ensure consistent and proportionate sentencing for all drug offences that come before courts.</p><p> </p><p>Simple cautions are a non-statutory disposal available to the police to dispose of any offence committed by an adult and designed for dealing with low level, mainly first time offending.</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice issues guidance on the process to be followed by the police when they are administering simple cautions for adult offenders. The latest guidance, issued in November 2013 following the Simple Cautions Review, states that the use of a simple caution for possession of class A drugs should only be given in exceptional cases following authorisation by a senior police officer. These will be cases where there were exceptional circumstances which would mean that it was not in the public interest to prosecute.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is legislating in the Criminal Justice and Courts Bill to place statutory restrictions on the use of cautions for certain serious offences.</p><p> </p><p>The number and proportion of offenders that were sentenced at all courts of a single offence of possession for class A, B and C drugs by sentence outcome in 2013, England and Wales can be viewed in the table below.</p><p> </p><p>The number of people cautioned for possession of class A, class B and class C drugs, in England and Wales, from 2009 to 2013 (latest data available) is accessible through the Ministry of Justice website and can be viewed through the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/311319/8-outcomes-by-offence.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/311319/8-outcomes-by-offence.xls</a>. Under the heading “Drug Offences” there are links to tables containing information relation to possession of class A, class B and class C drugs, including the number of cautions, from 2009-2013.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","208577 ; 208710 ; 208720","2014-10-14T13:44:22.5860674Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91194/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91194/answer","208577, 208720, 208715, 208710 table.xls","Number of offenders sentenced","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91194/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-09","Drugs: Misuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many and what proportion of offenders convicted of a single offence of possession of class C drugs received (a) a discharge, (b) a fine, (c) a community order, (d) a suspended prison sentence and (e) an immediate prison sentence in the most recent year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","208715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91195","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-10-13","<p>It is not possible to identify the amounts of victim surcharge imposed and collected which just relates to impositions made in the Crown Court or in relation to custodial sentences. This information could only be provided a disproportionate cost by carrying out a manual check of all financial impositions.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","208705","2014-10-13T15:05:24.674098Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91195/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91195/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91195/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-09","Fines: Surcharges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much in victim surcharge has been (a) imposed and (b) collected in cases involving Crown Court sentences of imprisonment since 1 October 2012.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","208712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91196","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-09-25","<p /> <p>Data are held centrally on the characteristics of the prison population on the last day of each month, so figures are not available for 23 December 2013 to 9 January 2014. Additionally, monthly and quarterly trends are typically compared using end of month and quarterly figures respectively.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","208707","2014-09-25T12:19:59.0171484Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91196/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91196/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91196/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-09","Belmarsh Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many (a) sentenced and (b) remand prisoners were held in HMP Belmarsh for the offence of criminal damage from 23 December 2013 to 9 January 2014.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","208717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91197","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-10-14","<p>Drug offending is serious in itself and drug abuse also underlies a huge volume of acquisitive and violent crime which can blight communities. Parliament sets the maximum penalty for an offence to deal with the worst possible case. Sentencing in individual cases is a matter for our independent courts, which must follow sentencing guidelines issued by the independent Sentencing Council. The guidelines provide a non-exhaustive list of factors to be taken into consideration and the court may depart from the guidelines in a particular case where it considers that it is in the interest of justice to do so.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-10-14T09:33:45.2010891Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91197/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91197/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91197/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-09","Drugs: Misuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, on what grounds offenders who received the maximum prison sentences for the possession of (a) class A and (b) class B drugs received those sentences in 2012.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","208719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91198","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-10-14","<p>Drug offending is serious in itself and drug abuse also underlies a huge volume of acquisitive and violent crime which can blight communities. The independent Sentencing Council issued a sentencing guideline on drug offences, effective from February 2012, which brought sentencing guidance together for the first time to help to ensure consistent and proportionate sentencing for all drug offences that come before courts.</p><p> </p><p>Simple cautions are a non-statutory disposal available to the police to dispose of any offence committed by an adult and designed for dealing with low level, mainly first time offending.</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice issues guidance on the process to be followed by the police when they are administering simple cautions for adult offenders. The latest guidance, issued in November 2013 following the Simple Cautions Review, states that the use of a simple caution for possession of class A drugs should only be given in exceptional cases following authorisation by a senior police officer. These will be cases where there were exceptional circumstances which would mean that it was not in the public interest to prosecute.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is legislating in the Criminal Justice and Courts Bill to place statutory restrictions on the use of cautions for certain serious offences.</p><p> </p><p>The number and proportion of offenders that were sentenced at all courts of a single offence of possession for class A, B and C drugs by sentence outcome in 2013, England and Wales can be viewed in the table below.</p><p> </p><p>The number of people cautioned for possession of class A, class B and class C drugs, in England and Wales, from 2009 to 2013 (latest data available) is accessible through the Ministry of Justice website and can be viewed through the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/311319/8-outcomes-by-offence.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/311319/8-outcomes-by-offence.xls</a>. Under the heading “Drug Offences” there are links to tables containing information relation to possession of class A, class B and class C drugs, including the number of cautions, from 2009-2013.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","208577 ; 208710 ; 208715","2014-10-14T13:44:22.8696476Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91198/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91198/answer","208577, 208720, 208715, 208710 table.xls","Number of offenders sentenced","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91198/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-09","Drugs: Misuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many and what proportion of offenders convicted of a single offence of possession of class B drugs received (a) a discharge, (b) a fine, (c) a community order, (d) a suspended prison sentence and (e) an immediate prison sentence in the most recent year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","208720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91199","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-11-18","<p>I am unable to disclose the information requested. Disclosure of this sensitive personal data could lead to individual prisoners being identified due to the low numbers matching the criteria.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","208706","2014-11-18T15:50:55.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91199/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91199/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91199/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-09","Belmarsh Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prisoners held in HMP Belmarsh for what offences were (a) over 70, (b) in a wheelchair, (c) using a walking frame and (d) recorded as having hernia problems from 23 December 2013 to 9 January 2014.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","208709"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91200","Ministry of Justice","true","2014-11-18","<p>Drug offending is serious in itself and drug abuse also underlies a huge volume of acquisitive and violent crime which can blight communities. Previous convictions, where they are recent and relevant, must be treated as an aggravating factor by the courts and will make the sentence more severe. The independent Sentencing Council issued a sentencing guideline on drug offences, effective from February 2012, which brought sentencing guidance together for the first time to help to ensure consistent and proportionate sentencing for all drug offences that come before courts.</p><p> </p><p>The table below shows the number of offenders sentenced to immediate custody for the possession of (a) class A, (b) class B and (c) class C drugs offence in England and Wales, for the 12 months ending March 2014, by the number of previous convictions.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-11-18T17:57:27.007Z","2015-02-17T10:01:49.473Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91200/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91200/answer","208713 - Number of previous convictions for A-C.xls","Immediate custody for drug offences","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91200/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91200/answer/previousversion/28630","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91200/answer/previousversion/28630","208713 table.xls","Immediate custody for drug offences","54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-09","Drugs: Misuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many previous convictions at the time of sentence each offender sentenced to immediate custody for a single offence of possession of (a) class A, (b) class B and (c) class C drugs had in the most recent year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","208713"
