tr><tr><td><p>Identity Issue</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Incorrect Documentation</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Licence Recall</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Misapplication Of Policy</p></td><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Misfiled Warrant</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>15</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Paperwork Error</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Recall Issue</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>13</p></td><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Remand Issue</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>9</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Unclear</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Unresolved Immigration Issues</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fail To Appear Warrant Overlooked</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Release Condition Not Met</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Outstanding Absconder</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Unknown/Not Recorded/Under Investigation</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>This data has been drawn from live incident files and is accurate on 30 September 2014. It is, however, subject to variance due to the nature of the live reporting system.</p><p> </p><p>Information on the number of prisoners, their offence(s) and period of sentence left to serve at the point at which they were released from prison in error that (a) have and (b) have not been returned to custody in each of the last five years is not readily available. In order to obtain this information, manual interrogation of the prisoners’ records and of a central administrative system would need to be carried out. This could only be achieved at disproportionate cost.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","208714","2014-10-21T16:37:45.2757592Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91206/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91206/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91206/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-09","Prisoners' Release","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prisoners sentenced for what offence have been released from prison in error while (a) being held on remand and (b) serving a custodial sentence in each of the last five years; and what the nature of the error was in each case.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","208711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91207","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-11-18","<p /> <p>The Government believes it is important that people consider what they want to happen to their property when they die. I would encourage people of all ages to ensure they have properly considered making a will so that, if the worst happens, their property is passed on in line with their wishes. We are currently considering what steps we can take to raise awareness of the importance of making a will.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-11-18T13:52:25.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91207/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91207/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91207/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-09","Wills","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps the Government is taking to encourage more people to make a will.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","208644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91208","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-11-18","<p>I am unable to disclose the information requested. Disclosure of this sensitive personal data could lead to individual prisoners being identified due to the low numbers matching the criteria.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","208709","2014-11-18T15:50:55.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91208/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91208/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91208/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-09","Brixton Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prisoners held in HMP Brixton for what offences were (a) over 70, (b) in a wheelchair, (c) using a walking frame and (d) recorded as having hernia problems from 9 January 2014 to 7 February 2014.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","208706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91209","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-09-30","<p /> <p>Applications for domestic violence protection orders in the Greater Manchester area are heard at Manchester, Bolton and Oldham Magistrates’ Courts. They are not heard at Bury and Rochdale Magistrates’ Court and it is not possible to seperately identify those from Bury or Rochdale.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-09-30T08:54:28.7743897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91209/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91209/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91209/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-09-09","Domestic Violence Protection Orders: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many applications for a domestic violence protection order were made to the Bury and Rochdale Magistrates' Court in the most recent 12 month period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","208677"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91210","Department of Health","false","2014-10-14","<p>NHS England is improving prison mental health services through nationally developed service specifications, which are being rolled out across the prison estate in England, ensuring that there are national standards against which services can be measured.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Identification of those offenders with problems including mental health, learning difficulties and other vulnerabilities by liaison and diversion services may facilitate relevant support to these offenders, rather than a criminal justice system intervention. This has potential to reduce caseload numbers and effectively divert away from custody or community sentences.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>NHS England has rolled out a new, all age national Liaison and Diversion standard service specification and operating model to 10 trial schemes, serving 22% of the English population. Following evaluation of these schemes by 2015 and Treasury approval of a full business case in 2015, NHS England will roll out to cover 100% coverage of the population by 2017-18.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Improving offender mental health is a priority for the Government, as set out in the mental health strategy <em>No Health, Without Mental Health </em>in 2011. We have acted upon the recommendations of Lord Bradley’s 2009 review of people with mental health problems and learning disabilities in the criminal justice system, to ensure that prisoners have the same access to mental health services as the rest of population.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In addition, the Government’s Mandate with NHS England commits NHS England to develop better healthcare services for people in the criminal justice system. We have also asked the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence to develop guidelines on improving the mental health for people in prison, which it expects to publish in 2016.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-10-14T15:05:20.0414767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91210/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91210/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91210/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-09-09","Prisons: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent steps his Department has taken to improve conditions for prisoners with mental health problems in prisons in England; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","208641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91211","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-09-12","<p>The Government recognises the contribution that people of faith can make to their own local communities and to wider society. Freedom of religious observance for all citizens is a fundamental principle of a free society and people draw on a range of sources to define and express their identity. The Government has no overarching role in regulating personal belief or faith. There are already several international days of prayer, i.e. All Saints Day and Women’s World Day of Prayer.</p><p> </p><p>As well as these, faith leaders regularly come together to pray for specific issues. Recently, Lord Ahmad took part in a prayer vigil at Westminster Cathedral for Iraq with leading members of faith communities from around the country.</p>","Bristol West","Stephen Williams",,"2014-09-12T13:26:17.9260262Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91211/answer","Biography information for Stephen Williams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91211/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91211/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-09-09","Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will have discussions with religious groups on reintroducing a National Day of Prayer to reflect on the terrorist threats the UK faces.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","208699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91212","Scotland Office","false","2014-09-12","<p> </p><p>This information could only be provided at disproportionate cost. Details of all Ministerial overseas travel is published on a quarterly basis.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-09-12T11:33:58.1893039Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91212/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91212/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91212/answer",,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-09-09","Domestic Visits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, pursuant to the Answer of 23 June 2014, Official Report, column 53W, on official visits, what domestic visits he and his predecessor have made since January 2013; and what the purpose of each such visit was.","false","Biography information for Sheila Gilmore","Edinburgh East","Sheila Gilmore","208669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91213","Women and Equalities","false","2014-09-12","<p> </p><p>Ministers and officials from the Government Equalities Office regularly meet a broad range of lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender stakeholders. Government Equalities Office officials met with representatives from the UK Intersex Association in June 2012.</p><p> </p>","East Dunbartonshire","Jo Swinson",,"2014-09-12T12:41:06.4656757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91213/answer","Biography information for Jo Swinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91213/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91213/answer",,,,,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2014-09-09","Intersex","1","House of Commons","To ask the Ministers for Women and Equalities, what meetings (a) she, (b) Ministers in her Department and (c) officials in her Department have had with individuals or groups representing intersex people.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","208685"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91214","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-12","<p /> <p /> <p>Each Work Programme statistical release gives a breakdown of provider performance against published minimum performance levels by payment group. These groups are assigned by the age of the claimant and the benefit they are in receipt of at the time of referral to the programme.</p><p>Information on the Work Programme split by age and contract can be found on the tabulation tool which (as well as the statistical release information) can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/work-programme-statistics--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/work-programme-statistics--2</a></p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-09-12T13:35:28.8448899Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91214/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91214/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91214/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-09","Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will make it his policy to release work programme provider performance data according to the age of participant.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","208688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91215","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-13","<p>The recent consultation <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/321921/bis-14-861-future-development-of-loans-in-further-education-consultation-v2.pdf" target="_blank">Further Education – Future Development of Loans</a> included discussion of this question; both whether the scope of loans should be expanded to cover 19 to 23 year olds and whether loans should be made available for all level 2 qualifications where learners are not entitled to full grant funding. The government response to this consultation is due late autumn.</p><p>Full funding will continue to focus on English and maths provision for all adults who need it, on young adults, and the unemployed where skills training will help them to enter and progress in work. Where young adults are taking a second qualification, or are aged 24 or over, there is an expectation that they or their employer share some of the costs of that learning.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2014-10-13T15:23:24.973743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91215/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91215/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91215/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-09-09","Education: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will bring forward proposals to prioritise funding for second qualifications for those with the lowest levels of work experience and skills.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","208697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91216","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-12","Jobcentre Plus operate a number of different approaches to support Older Claimants in getting back to work and this includes measures aimed at improving digital knowledge and awareness to support people in modern recruitment processes. Local schemes in place include intensive IT courses to cover IT fundamentals such as the use of MS Word, emailing and the internet. Work Programme providers have the freedom to develop their support for claimants, including older jobseekers; this can include support with online recruitment processes.","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-09-12T12:03:47.5295785Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91216/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91216/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91216/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-09","Older People: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to support older jobseekers in going through online recruitment processes.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","208698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91217","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-12","<p>Prior to referral to the Work Programme, Jobcentre work coaches offer a comprehensive range of support to individuals, including older jobseekers.</p><p>There are no plans to bring forward legislative proposals to allow early entry to the work programme for unemployed older people nor do we have plans to introduce a new Work Programme payment group for older jobseekers.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","208694","2014-09-12T13:53:00.1348851Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91217/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91217/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91217/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-09","Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to allow early entry to the work programme for unemployed older people.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","208691"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91218","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-12","<p /> <p /> <p>We do not collect data about disabled people using Access to Work as requested, therefore the information is not available.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","208692","2014-09-12T13:04:30.7203005Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91218/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91218/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91218/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-09","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many disabled people have received new support from the Access to Work scheme to participate in internships, traineeships and work placements in each month since September 2013.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","208695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91219","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-12","<p>Prior to referral to the Work Programme, Jobcentre work coaches offer a comprehensive range of support to individuals, including older jobseekers.</p><p>There are no plans to bring forward legislative proposals to allow early entry to the work programme for unemployed older people nor do we have plans to introduce a new Work Programme payment group for older jobseekers.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","208691","2014-09-12T13:53:00.2598845Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91219/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91219/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91219/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-09","Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will bring forward proposals for a new Work Programme payment group for older jobseekers.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","208694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91220","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-10-13","<p /> <p>The information requested is in the attached tables; numbers of new starts to Access to Work 2012-13 and 2013-14.</p><p>These figures are a breakdown of the published official statistics available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/access-to-work-statistics-on-recipients--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/access-to-work-statistics-on-recipients--2</a></p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-10-13T14:10:47.3952267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91220/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91220/answer","UIN 208696 - New Starts Access to Work 2012-2014..pdf","New Starts Access to Work 2012-2014.","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91220/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-09","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many new beneficiaries of the Access to Work scheme had (a) mental health conditions, (b) physical impairments and (c) sensory impairments as the main disabling condition recorded by his Department in each of the last 24 months.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","208696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91221","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-12","<p>We keep the costs under continuous review and this information will be used to support the future development of unit cost benchmarks.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-09-12T10:14:16.3361593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91221/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91221/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91221/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-09","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how the costs of administering and providing personal independence payment decisions are monitored and value for money reviewed for improvement.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","208739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91222","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-12","<p>The information requested is not held. All HSE construction inspectors are trained to enforce the management and control of asbestos by duty holders and routinely deal with asbestos issues in their everyday work. The majority of construction inspectors are further trained to inspect notified licensed asbestos removal work. The table provides the average number of full-time equivalent operational inspectors who visited construction sites on a day-to-day basis for the years 2010/11 to 2013/14.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>2013/14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>147</p></td><td><p>141</p></td><td><p>137</p></td><td><p>129</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-09-12T10:43:19.0678283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91222/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91222/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91222/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-09","Asbestos","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many full-time Health and Safety Executive officers were employed to monitor asbestos removal in each month since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Steve Rotheram","Liverpool, Walton","Steve Rotheram","208726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91223","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-12","<p /> <p /> <p>The costs of administering the PIP assessment process were published in the NAO report in February 2014.</p>","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-09-12T09:54:14.2397643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91223/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91223/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91223/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-09","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the average cost of a personal independence payment decision, including assessment costs and departmental administration.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","208738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91224","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-12","HSE does not hold records on the number of occasions when site visits occur outside normal business working hours.","Forest of Dean","Mr Mark Harper",,"2014-09-12T11:21:20.9440839Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91224/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Harper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91224/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91224/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-09","Asbestos","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what records his Department holds on the number of occasions on which Health and Safety Executive asbestos removal inspectors have undertaken visits to sites outside normal business working hours.","false","Biography information for Steve Rotheram","Liverpool, Walton","Steve Rotheram","208728"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91225","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-12","<p /> <p /> <p>We do not collect data about disabled people using Access to Work as requested, therefore the information is not available.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","208695","2014-09-12T13:04:30.6421722Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91225/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91225/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91225/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-09","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many disabled people are using Access to Work support for a (a) work trial, (b) work experience opportunity under the Youth contract, (c)  supported internship, (d) traineeship and (e) pre-employment training work placement.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","208692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91226","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-09-12","<p /> <p /> <p>Work Programme providers deliver personalised support, tailored to the individual needs of participants. Providers are bound through the terms of their contract to prevent unlawful discrimination and promote equality of opportunity in respect of age.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Jobcentre Plus have the freedom to use a range of innovative measures to help older claimants overcome any barriers associated with age. Local schemes include IT support aimed specifically at older people; dedicated advisers for those aged over 50; and help to convert dated qualifications into certifications that are relevant for modern employers.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-09-12T13:35:02.6156398Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91226/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91226/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91226/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-09-09","Age: Discrimination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to help Jobcentre Plus, Work Programme and voluntary providers to tackle age discrimination.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","208702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91227","Attorney General","false","2014-10-13","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) case outcome records include an allocation of a reason for cases not resulting in a conviction, including the numbers where the judge ordered an acquittal. Judge ordered acquittals comprise cases discontinued, where no evidence was offered, the indictment was stayed or all charges were left to lie on file.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Further to the Answer provided on 1 September 2014, published in Hansard, Official Report, column 32W, on Crown Courts, the number of defendants, by reason, in the ‘Homicide’ category with an outcome of ‘Offer no Evidence’ or ‘Judge Ordered Acquittal’, during 2013-14 is shown in the attached table. The data represent case outcomes recorded by the 13 regional Areas of the Crown Prosecution Service</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Swindon","Mr Robert Buckland",,"2014-10-13T14:40:55.6231843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91227/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91227/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91227/answer",,,,,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-09-09","Homicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, pursuant to the Answer of 1 September 2014, Official Report, column 32W, on Crown Courts, what the reasons were for the (a) Crown Prosecution Service offering no evidence and (b) judge ordering acquittals in each of the cases in the homicide category.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","208789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91228","Attorney General","false","2014-10-13","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) maintains a central record of prosecution outcomes with reference to 12 Principal Offence Categories which indicate the most serious offence a defendant is charged with at finalisation, in the CPS Case Management Information System.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Principal Offence Category comprises a range of individual offences. These cannot be disaggregated to report prosecution outcomes by a specific offence.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Further to the Answer provided on 16 July 2014, published in Hansard, Official Report, column 678W, on Crown Courts, the number of defendants allocated a Principal Offence Category of ‘Homicide’ in each of the last six years, is shown in the attached table.</p><p> </p>","South Swindon","Mr Robert Buckland",,"2014-10-13T14:34:41.7687133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91228/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91228/answer","Table PQ 208790.docx","Table: Homicide  - PQ 208790","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91228/answer",,,,,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-09-09","Homicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, pursuant to the Answer of 16 July 2014, Official Report, column 678W, on Crown Courts, how many defendants included in the figures for each of the years from 2008 to 2013 were charged with homicide.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","208790"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91229","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-14","<p>Responsibility for investigating potential breaches of UK export controls falls to HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC). I am assured that HMRC fully and properly considered the alleged breaches at the 2013 Defence and Security Equipment International exhibition, as they would in any case where potential breaches are detected or where there are credible allegations of an offence. In this instance, HMRC determined that further action was neither appropriate nor viable.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2014-10-14T16:00:06.1929871Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91229/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91229/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91229/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-09-09","Arms Trade: Trade Fairs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the letter he received in February 2014 from the law firm Hodge Jones and Allen setting out alleged breaches of law at the Defence and Security Equipment International arms fair in 2013; whether any enforcement actions have been taken in response to this letter; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","208783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/91230","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-10-21","<p>Recent data for years since the tuition fee reforms and access agreements is not yet available, but the latest data from the Universities and Colleges Admissions Service (UCAS) shows that entry rates to higher education for all ethnic groups in 2013 had increased and overall, there was a much higher representation of black and minority ethnic groups in university than in the overall population of England.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The table below shows the figures before these changes.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><br></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>Estimated percentage of maintained school pupils aged 15 in each ethnic group who progressed to Oxford, Cambridge or Russell Group institutions by age 19</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="4"><p>Progression by age 19 in</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2008/09</p></td><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>2011/12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Asian/Asian British</strong></p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oxford</p></td><td><p>0.2%</p></td><td><p>0.2%</p></td><td><p>0.2%</p></td><td><p>0.2%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cambridge</p></td><td><p>0.3%</p></td><td><p>0.3%</p></td><td><p>0.3%</p></td><td><p>0.3%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Russell Group</p></td><td><p>11.4%</p></td><td><p>11.5%</p></td><td><p>10.6%</p></td><td><p>10.7%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Black/Black British</strong></p></td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oxford</p></td><td><p>0.1%</p></td><td><p>0.1%</p></td><td><p>0.1%</p></td><td><p>0.1%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cambridge</p></td><td><p>0.1%</p></td><td><p>0.1%</p></td><td><p>0.1%</p></td><td><p>0.1%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Russell Group</p></td><td><p>4.6%</p></td><td><p>4.2%</p></td><td><p>4.4%</p></td><td><p>4.1%</p></